http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Man-killed-in-accident-near-Aluva/article14013872.ece

A 60-year-old unidentified man was killed after being run over by a truck near Aluva here on Thursday.According to the police, the man, who eked out a living by collecting plastic waste, was found lying in a pool of blood on the National Highway near the Aluva market. Preliminary investigations revealed that the man could have been trapped under a truck while sleeping on the roadside in the wee hours of the day.“Investigations showed that the victim had been sleeping under one of the parked trucks here and was run over by the same vehicle when its driver resumed its journey,” officials said. A case has been registered and a follow-up investigation is on.